  "Idea": "We propose an advanced iteration of TAB-ROBUST—now reimagined as a dynamic, adaptive benchmarking framework called \\textbf{TAB-ROBUST+}: A Cognitive Curriculum for Diagnosing and Developing Robust TableQA Systems. This framework extends beyond static evaluation by introducing \\textit{Adversarial Learning Curricula} (ALC) that evolve in tandem with model capabilities. Building on the original human-annotated adversarial dataset across headers, content, and questions, TAB-ROBUST+ integrates three novel components: (1) \\textbf{Vulnerability-Aware Perturbation Sequencing}, which uses diagnostic probes to identify a model’s dominant failure mode (e.g., Structural Invariance Failure) and then serves up progressively harder perturbation chains targeting that weakness; (2) \\textbf{Cross-Modal Consistency Enforcement}, where every perturbation to a table (e.g., header synonymy) is mirrored by linguistically aligned modifications in the question (e.g., corresponding lexical shifts), ensuring ecological coherence missing in prior benchmarks; and (3) \\textbf{Curriculum Scheduler with Feedback Loop}, which adjusts difficulty based on real-time performance, akin to human tutoring systems. The benchmark includes a \\textit{Robustness Growth Score} (RGS), measuring not just final accuracy but the rate and stability of improvement across curriculum stages. We further release \\textit{AutoCura}, an automated curriculum generator powered by LLMs that synthesizes personalized adversarial training paths using the annotated taxonomy and model diagnostics. To validate, we evaluate six leading TableQA architectures (including TAPAS, Picard, and LLM-based solvers) under both standard and curriculum-based training regimes. Results show that models trained on adaptive curricula achieve higher zero-shot robustness on unseen perturbation types and exhibit flatter degradation curves under chain attacks. Crucially, RGS correlates strongly with out-of-distribution generalization, suggesting it captures deeper robustness than static metrics. By unifying evaluation, diagnosis, and development into a single framework, TAB-ROBUST+ redefines robustness benchmarks as active learning environments rather than passive test suites—paving the way for self-diagnosing, self-improving AI systems in data-rich domains.",
